de.charite.compbio.jannovar.annotation

Enum OldVariantType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<OldVariantType>
      • de.charite.compbio.jannovar.annotation.OldVariantType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<OldVariantType>

    public enum OldVariantType
extends Enum<OldVariantType>
    Enumeration of the old Jannovar variant types (i.e. those in the originally published version). These are only here for compatibility with the output of the old version.
    Author:
    Manuel Holtgrewe

      • priorityLevel

        public int priorityLevel()
        The preference level for annotations is
        1. exonic (1): FS_DELETION, FS_INSERTION, NON_FS_SUBSTITUTION, FS_SUBSTITUTION, MISSENSE, NON_FS_DELETION, NON_FS_INSERTION, STOPGAIN, STOPLOSS, FS_DUPLICATION, NON_FS_DUPLICATION, START_LOSS, START_GAIN.
        2. splicing (1): SPLICING.
        3. ncRNA (2):ncRNA_EXONIC, ncRNA_SPLICING.
        4. UTR3 (3): UTR3
        5. UTR5 (4): UTR5
        6. synonymous (5): SYNONYMOUS
        7. intronic (6): INTRONIC
        8. intronic (7): ncRNA_INTRONIC.
        9. upstream (8): UPSTREAM.
        10. downstream (9): DOWNSTREAM.
        11. intergenic (10): INTERGENIC.
        12. error (11): ERROR.
        Returns:
        priority level for sorting lists of variants.

      • isTopPriorityVariant

        public boolean isTopPriorityVariant()
        We do not know, actually, whether any given variant is pathogenic if we just judge its pathogenicity class. But on the whole, the VariantTypes that have been given the priority level one will include the lion's share of true pathogenic mutations. This function returns true if a variantType has pathogenicity level one, otherwise false. It is intended to be used by client code to help sort variants by predicted pathogenicity, in the knowledge that occasionally we will be wrong, e.g., a variant of priority level 3 might actually be the disease causing mutation.
        Returns:
        true if a variantType has pathogenicity level one, otherwise false

      • getPrioritySortedList

        public static OldVariantType[] getPrioritySortedList()
